<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-1796] Infiniteloop BaseParser.java:1010</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1796</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;infinite loop at org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.parseCOSHexString(BaseParser.java:1010)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;private final COSString parseCOSHexString() throws IOException&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
            // read till the closing bracket was found&lt;br/&gt;
            do &lt;br/&gt;
            &lt;/p&gt;
{
                c = pdfSource.read();
            }
&lt;p&gt; while ( c != &apos;&amp;gt;&apos; );&lt;br/&gt;
...   &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if pdfSource.read() returns EOF, the loop never terminates;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Testcase:&lt;br/&gt;
PDDocument doc = PDDocument.load (new FileInputStream(&quot;...&quot;));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2 real world pdf-files that cause the loop could be attached; do not know if their PDF is completely valid, but at least they are displayed via Preview in MacOSX.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
