&lt;p&gt;Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13841054" author="msahyoun" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 07:18:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
I added a fix in revision 1548387 for the current trunk. Could you verify if it works for you?&lt;br/&gt;
BR&lt;br/&gt;
Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13841085" author="maschau" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 08:12:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi Maruan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks a lot for your fast response; think that the fixed line:&lt;br/&gt;
... } while ( c != &apos;&amp;gt;&apos; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; c &amp;lt; 0 ); ...&lt;br/&gt;
should more look like&lt;br/&gt;
... } while ( c != &apos;&amp;gt;&apos; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; c &amp;gt;= 0 ); ...&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
trying to attach the affected files,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;kind regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Manfred&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13841146" author="msahyoun" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 10:08:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Manfred,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I added a fix to the fix &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; With that applied the parser no longer has an infinite loop using your files. The file dls.pdf is handled fine e.g. extracting text. rsag.pdf has some more issues. As there is a newer parser which is more inline with the PDF spec you should use &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PDDocument.loadNonSeq() instead of PDDocument.load()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you&#8217;re fine can we close the issue as I think the described one is solved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BR and thanks for your report.&lt;br/&gt;
Maruan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13841696" author="tilman" created="Fri, 6 Dec 2013 20:58:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1668&quot; title=&quot;Loading a Russian PDF never finishes &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1668&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1668&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. And yes, the solution works too. You can close both &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;(Edit) And also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1585&quot; title=&quot;org.apache.pdfbox.util.PDFTextStripper.getText() causes thread to block indefinitely&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1585&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1585&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
